  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_11' aria-label=\" Communidade of Tivim, Tivim, Bardez Goa versus State of Goa & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('11','2025','2025_7_497_504','2025INSC835'); ><font size='4'> <strong>COMMUNIDADE OF TIVIM, TIVIM, BARDEZ GOA<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF GOA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 497</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 835</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002872025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SUDHANSHU DHULIA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, K. VINOD CHANDRAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the Administrative Tribunal was correct in its refusal to grant the appellant, permission to compromise proceedings with the private respondents in terms of Article 154 (3) of the Code of Comunidades. Headnotes&dagger; Goa, Daman and Diu Agricultural Tenancy Act, Comunidades &ndash; Art.154(3) &ndash; Goa Land Use (Regulation) Act, 1991 &ndash; By the order dated 13.04.2023, the Administrative Tribunal, Goa refused to grant permission to the appellant to compromise proceedings instituted by the private respondents herein (respondent nos. 3 to 11) &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 14-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 9470/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('11','2025','2025_7_497_504','2025INSC835','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Spli